review_blob: Beautiful aromatic first impression, hints of apparent hoppiness tickle my nose immediately after cracking my first bottle.  Nice medium head upon first pouring that likes to cling loosely to the side of my glass.  Reminds me of the glorious Celebration ale in terms of hoppiness, only a bit maltier/sweeter.  Not all that fruity, but definite undertones of bittersweet caramel.  Definite alcohol warmth once it descends past the throat.
